In [7]:
import geoplot
Cairo_data['pop_per_area'] = Cairo_data.Population * 10**3/Cairo_data.Area

# Note: this code sample requires geoplot>=0.4.0.
geoplot.choropleth(
    Cairo_data,
    hue=Cairo_data['pop_per_area'],
    cmap='jet',
    legend=True,
    figsize=(18, 9)
)

In [10]:
map_ = folium.Map(location=[30, 31.5],
                  zoom_start=10)
# add Population Density layer :
map_.choropleth(
 geo_data=Cairo_data,
 name='Choropleth',
 data=Cairo_data,
 columns=['Name','pop_per_area'],
 key_on="feature.properties.Name",
 fill_color='YlGnBu',
 fill_opacity=0.8,
 line_opacity=0.7,
 legend_name='Population density k person/km^2',
 smooth_factor=0
)
folium.LayerControl().add_to(map_)
map_

Adding Some Interactive tools¶

In [11]:
style_function = lambda x: {'fillColor': '#ffffff', 
                            'color':'#000000', 
                            'fillOpacity': 0.1, 
                            'weight': 0.1}
highlight_function = lambda x: {'fillColor': '#000000', 
                                'color':'#000000', 
                                'fillOpacity': 0.50, 
                                'weight': 0.1}

NIL = folium.features.GeoJson(
    Cairo_data,
    style_function=style_function, 
    control=False,
    highlight_function=highlight_function, 
    tooltip=folium.features.GeoJsonTooltip(
        fields=['Name','Population', 'Area'],
        aliases=['Region name','Population', 'Area'],
        style=("background-color: white; color: #333333; font-family: arial; font-size: 12px; padding: 10px;") 
    )
)
map_.add_child(NIL)
map_.keep_in_front(NIL)
map_
